  <header class="top">
    <a class="back" href="/">← Fariborz Aref</a>
    <span class="here">The Birth Lottery</span>
  </header>

  <main id="main">
    <div class="wrap">

      <section class="hero">
        <span class="eyebrow">The Structure of Life Chances</span>
        <h1>The Birth Lottery</h1>
        <p class="thesis">
          You did not choose where you were born. Almost nothing about your life mattered more.
          Press the button below and be born, at random, into today's world — weighted, honestly,
          by where people actually are. <em>Then ask what you did to deserve the result.</em>
        </p>
        <p class="pull">Merit begins after the lottery. The lottery decides most of the outcome.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- LOTTERY -->
      <section class="lottery rv">
        <div class="stage">
          <div class="stage-kicker">You are born in…</div>
          <div class="stage-name" id="name">—</div>
          <div class="stage-band" id="band"></div>
          <div class="odds" id="odds"></div>

          <div class="stats" id="stats">
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="stat-top"><span class="stat-label">Life expectancy at birth</span><span class="stat-val" id="v-life"></span></div>
              <div class="track"><div class="fill" id="f-life" style="background:var(--accent)"></div></div>
              <div class="rangelabels"><span>50 yrs</span><span>85 yrs</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="stat-top"><span class="stat-label">Income per person (PPP)</span><span class="stat-val" id="v-inc"></span></div>
              <div class="track"><div class="fill" id="f-inc" style="background:var(--navy)"></div></div>
              <div class="rangelabels"><span>$800</span><span>$90,000</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="stat-top"><span class="stat-label">Years of schooling (avg adult)</span><span class="stat-val" id="v-sch"></span></div>
              <div class="track"><div class="fill" id="f-sch" style="background:var(--gold)"></div></div>
              <div class="rangelabels"><span>2 yrs</span><span>15 yrs</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="takeaway" id="takeaway"></p>

          <div class="stage-controls">
            <button class="btn" id="born" type="button">Be born into the world</button>
            <button class="btn ghost" id="again" type="button" style="display:none">Be born again</button>
          </div>
          <div class="tally" id="tally"></div>
        </div>
        <p class="note">
          Illustrative figures, rounded, from World Bank (income, life expectancy) and UNDP (schooling),
          c. 2023, across a population-weighted sample of ~5 billion people. Approximate — verify against
          current sources before citing.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- FACTS -->
      <section class="facts rv">
        <h2>By the numbers</h2>
        <p class="sub">The shape of the world you were just born into.</p>
        <div class="factgrid">
          <div class="fact">
            <div class="big">76% / 2%</div>
            <p>The richest 10% of humanity hold about three-quarters of all wealth. The poorest half hold roughly two percent.</p>
            <cite>World Inequality Report 2022</cite>
          </div>
          <div class="fact">
            <div class="big">52%</div>
            <p>Share of global income captured by the top 10%. The bottom half of the world earns about 8.5%.</p>
            <cite>World Inequality Report 2022</cite>
          </div>
          <div class="fact">
            <div class="big">&gt; 50%</div>
            <p>Share of the variation in global incomes explained by a single fact: the country a person was born in.</p>
            <cite>Milanović, Global Inequality</cite>
          </div>
          <div class="fact">
            <div class="big">~700M</div>
            <p>People — nearly one in eleven — living on less than $2.15 a day, the World Bank's line for extreme poverty.</p>
            <cite>World Bank, 2022</cite>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ESSAY -->
      <section class="essay rv">
        <h2>Why this is the sociologist's question</h2>
        <p class="lineage">A century of sociology rests on one refusal: the refusal to mistake a person's position for a person's merit.</p>
        <p>
          Marx read inequality in the ownership of capital; Weber, in the interlocking of class, status, and
          power; Durkheim, in the way whole societies cohere or come apart. Different lenses, one shared
          conviction — that life chances are <em>structured</em>, distributed before the individual acts,
          by institutions and history rather than desert.
        </p>
        <p>
          The birth lottery is that conviction made visible. The country you land in fixes, on average, how
          long you will live, how far you will study, and how much you will earn — and it does so before you
          have done anything at all. This is not an argument against effort. It is an argument about what
          effort is <em>added to</em>: a starting line that is nowhere near the same for everyone.
        </p>
        <p>
          My own work asks the next question — not only how unequal the world is, but what <em>reduces</em> it:
          which institutions, which welfare arrangements, which forms of community capacity turn a brutal
          starting position into a survivable one. Inequality is structured. So, therefore, is the work of
          undoing it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- CLOSING -->
      <section class="closing rv">
        <p class="ai">
          You were born once, without choosing. <b>Everyone reading this drew a ticket too — and most of the
          world drew worse than you.</b> The measure of a society is what it does about that.
        </p>
        <div class="sources">
          <h3>Sources</h3>
          World Inequality Report 2022 (wir2022.wid.world) · World Bank, World Development Indicators &amp; Poverty
          data · UNDP, Human Development Report · B. Milanović, <i>Global Inequality</i> (2016). Country figures are
          rounded approximations for illustration.
        </div>
        <div class="sig"><a href="/">← Return to fariborzaref.github.io</a> · The Birth Lottery · Fariborz Aref</div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <script>
    (function () {
      // reveal
      if (!window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches) {
        var io = new IntersectionObserver(function (es) { es.forEach(function (e) { if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('in'); io.unobserve(e.target); } }); }, { rootMargin: '0px 0px -10% 0px', threshold: 0.08 });
        document.querySelectorAll('.rv').forEach(function (n) { io.observe(n); });
      }

      // country data — rounded approximations, c. 2023
      // n=name, pop=millions, gni=income per capita PPP (US$), life=life expectancy, sch=mean years schooling
      var C = [
        { n: 'India', pop: 1428, gni: 8300, life: 67, sch: 6.6 },
        { n: 'China', pop: 1425, gni: 21000, life: 78, sch: 7.6 },
        { n: 'the United States', pop: 340, gni: 76000, life: 77, sch: 13.7 },
        { n: 'Indonesia', pop: 277, gni: 14000, life: 68, sch: 8.6 },
        { n: 'Pakistan', pop: 240, gni: 6400, life: 66, sch: 4.5 },
        { n: 'Nigeria', pop: 224, gni: 5700, life: 53, sch: 7.2 },
        { n: 'Brazil', pop: 216, gni: 18000, life: 75, sch: 8.3 },
        { n: 'Bangladesh', pop: 173, gni: 8400, life: 74, sch: 7.4 },
        { n: 'Russia', pop: 144, gni: 32000, life: 70, sch: 12.8 },
        { n: 'Mexico', pop: 128, gni: 21000, life: 75, sch: 9.2 },
        { n: 'Ethiopia', pop: 127, gni: 2800, life: 65, sch: 3.2 },
        { n: 'Japan', pop: 123, gni: 48000, life: 84, sch: 13.4 },
        { n: 'the DR Congo', pop: 102, gni: 1300, life: 59, sch: 6.8 },
        { n: 'Germany', pop: 84, gni: 63000, life: 81, sch: 14.1 },
        { n: 'Chad', pop: 18, gni: 1600, life: 53, sch: 2.6 },
        { n: 'Burundi', pop: 13, gni: 800, life: 62, sch: 3.1 },
        { n: 'Switzerland', pop: 8.8, gni: 84000, life: 84, sch: 13.9 }
      ];
      var TOTAL = C.reduce(function (a, c) { return a + c.pop; }, 0);
      var HIGH = C.filter(function (c) { return c.gni >= 25000; }).reduce(function (a, c) { return a + c.pop; }, 0);
      var highPct = Math.round(HIGH / TOTAL * 100);

      function pick() { var r = Math.random() * TOTAL, acc = 0; for (var i = 0; i < C.length; i++) { acc += C[i].pop; if (r <= acc) return C[i]; } return C[C.length - 1]; }
      function band(g) { return g < 2500 ? 'a low-income country' : g < 8000 ? 'a lower-middle-income country' : g < 25000 ? 'an upper-middle-income country' : 'a high-income country'; }
      function logfill(g) { var lo = Math.log(800), hi = Math.log(90000); return Math.max(2, Math.min(100, (Math.log(g) - lo) / (hi - lo) * 100)); }
      function money(g) { return '$' + g.toLocaleString(); }

      var nameEl = document.getElementById('name'), bandEl = document.getElementById('band'), oddsEl = document.getElementById('odds'),
          statsEl = document.getElementById('stats'), takeEl = document.getElementById('takeaway'), tallyEl = document.getElementById('tally'),
          bornBtn = document.getElementById('born'), againBtn = document.getElementById('again');
      var vLife = document.getElementById('v-life'), vInc = document.getElementById('v-inc'), vSch = document.getElementById('v-sch');
      var fLife = document.getElementById('f-life'), fInc = document.getElementById('f-inc'), fSch = document.getElementById('f-sch');

      var births = 0, highCount = 0, spinning = false;

      function reveal(c) {
        nameEl.textContent = c.n.replace(/^the /, 'the '); nameEl.classList.remove('spin');
        bandEl.textContent = 'Born into ' + band(c.gni) + '.';
        oddsEl.textContent = 'Your odds of landing here: about ' + (c.pop / TOTAL * 100).toFixed(1) + '%.';
        vLife.textContent = c.life + ' years'; vInc.textContent = money(c.gni); vSch.textContent = c.sch.toFixed(1) + ' years';
        statsEl.classList.add('show');
        requestAnimationFrame(function () {
          fLife.style.width = Math.max(2, Math.min(100, (c.life - 50) / 35 * 100)) + '%';
          fInc.style.width = logfill(c.gni) + '%';
          fSch.style.width = Math.max(2, Math.min(100, (c.sch - 2) / 13 * 100)) + '%';
        });
        var high = c.gni >= 25000;
        takeEl.textContent = high
          ? 'You won a lottery you never entered. Most of humanity never draws this ticket — and you did nothing to earn it.'
          : (c.gni < 2500
            ? 'Through no choice of your own, the odds just narrowed — in schooling, in health, in years of life itself.'
            : 'A middle draw. Comfortable by the standards of history, precarious by the standards of the rich world — and, again, not chosen.');
        takeEl.classList.add('show');
        births++; if (high) highCount++;
        tallyEl.innerHTML = 'You have been born <b>' + births + '</b> ' + (births === 1 ? 'time' : 'times') +
          '. Times you landed in a high-income country: <b>' + highCount + '</b>. ' +
          '(In this world, only about ' + highPct + '% of people are born into one.)';
        againBtn.style.display = ''; bornBtn.style.display = 'none';
      }

      function run() {
        if (spinning) return; spinning = true;
        statsEl.classList.remove('show'); takeEl.classList.remove('show');
        bandEl.textContent = ''; oddsEl.textContent = '';
        nameEl.classList.add('spin');
        var ticks = 0, target = 16 + Math.floor(Math.random() * 6);
        var iv = setInterval(function () {
          nameEl.textContent = C[Math.floor(Math.random() * C.length)].n.replace(/^the /, '');
          ticks++;
          if (ticks >= target) { clearInterval(iv); spinning = false; reveal(pick()); }
        }, 55);
      }
      bornBtn.addEventListener('click', run);
      againBtn.addEventListener('click', run);
    })();
  </script>
